\begin{array}{c|c|c}2010 & 2011 & 2012 \\\hline 50 & 20 & 30 \\\end{array}
100\times\left(\frac{|30-50|}{50}\right)\quad?
100\times\left(\frac{|30-50|}{50}\right)=100\times\left(\frac{20}{50}\right)=40\%.
100\times\left(\frac{30-50}{50}\right)=100\times\left(\frac{-20}{50}\right)=-40\%.
